loin /lɔɪn/

(loins) 

1. N-VAR Loin or a loin is a piece of meat which comes from the back or sides of an animal, near the tail end. 腰 

例： Heat the honey and brush it on to the outside of the loin. 加热蜂蜜，将其涂抹在背脊上。 

例： ...roast loin of venison. ...烧烤鹿肉背脊肉。 

2. N-PLURAL Someone's loins are the front part of their body between their waist and legs, especially their sexual parts. 耻骨区(尤指性器官) [文学性，老式]

